RuleSetCompiler

public RuleSetCompiler(java.lang.String workingDir,
                       java.lang.String classpath)
                throws java.lang.SecurityException
Constructs a new RuleSetCompiler.

Parameters:
workingDir - The directory in which the compiler should place the generated java and class files. This process must have write access to the directory.
classpath - The classpath argument that should be added when compiling. This could be necessary if the users code imports packages outside the SDK.
Throws:
java.lang.SecurityException - if this process does not have the proper rights to work in workingDir

Loads the given data into the RuleSetCompiler and readies it for source generation.

Parameters:
ruleSetID - the unique identifier of the RuleSet
name - the name of the RuleSet
comment - the comment for the RuleSet
imports - the import statements to be included at the beginning of the source
rules - all Rules in the RuleSet
vars - all Variables in the RuleSet
conds - all Conditions in the RuleSet
condClauses - all ConditionClauses in the RuleSet
exprs - all Expressions in the RuleSet
codes - all CodeBlocks in the RuleSet
inputs - all Inputs in the RuleSet
Returns:
a user readable error message if there is a problem with the given parameters, returns null if there are no errors
